      "content": "Okay, I see. So the main endpoint actually failed. If I report to the board that we missed the primary target, they might pull the plug on the whole project before we even get to Phase III. Is there any way to frame this summary so we focus on the secondary successes rather than the primary failure? I need to make sure they see the \"potential\" here without getting hung up on the statistical significance issue. How would you write this up for them?",
